description: The story of the final Emperor of China.

title: The Report
description: Idealistic Senate staffer Daniel J. Jones, tasked by his boss to lead an investigation into the CIA's post 9/11 Detention and Interrogation Program, uncovers shocking secrets.

title: Deliver Us from Evil
description: New York police officer Ralph Sarchie investigates a series of crimes. He joins forces with an unconventional priest, schooled in the rites of exorcism, to combat the possessions that are terrorizing their city.

title: Percy
description: A Canadian farmer takes on a giant corporation after their GMOs interfere with his crops.

title: Midnight Express
description: Billy Hayes, an American college student, is caught smuggling drugs out of Turkey and thrown into prison.

title: Tiger King: Murder, Mayhem and Madness
description: A rivalry between big cat eccentrics takes a dark turn when Joe Exotic, a controversial animal park boss, is caught in a murder-for-hire plot.

title: Ray
description: The story of the life and career of the legendary rhythm and blues musician Ray Charles, from his humble beginnings in the South, where he went blind at age seven, to his meteoric rise to stardom during the 1950s and 1960s.

title: Rob Roy
description: In 1713 Scotland, Rob Roy MacGregor is wronged by a nobleman and his nephew, becomes an outlaw in search of revenge while fleeing the Redcoats, and faces charges of being a Jacobite.

title: Selena
description: The true story of Selena, a Texas-born Tejano singer who rose from cult status to performing at the Astrodome, as well as having chart topping albums on the Latin music charts.

title: Roots
description: A dramatization of author Alex Haley's family line from ancestor Kunta Kinte's enslavement to his descendants' liberation.

title: The Walk
description: In 1974, high-wire artist Philippe Petit recruits a team of people to help him realize his dream: to walk the immense void between the World Trade Center towers.

title: Masterminds
description: A guard at an armored car company in the Southern U.S. organizes one of the biggest bank heists in American history. Based on the October 1997 Loomis Fargo robbery.

title: All the President's Men
description: "The Washington Post" reporters Bob Woodward and Carl Bernstein uncover the details of the Watergate scandal that leads to President Richard Nixon's resignation.

title: Soul Surfer
description: Teenage surfer Bethany Hamilton overcomes the odds and her own fears of returning to the water after losing her left arm in a shark attack.

title: John Adams
description: The life of one of the USA's Founding Fathers, its second President, and his role in the nation's first 50 years.

title: Frida
description: A biography of artist Frida Kahlo, who channeled the pain of a crippling injury and her tempestuous marriage into her work.

title: La Vie En Rose
description: Biopic of the iconic French singer Édith Piaf. Raised by her grandmother in a brothel, she was discovered while singing on a street corner at the age of 19. Despite her success, Piaf's life was filled with tragedy.

title: Blonde
description: A fictionalized chronicle of the inner life of Marilyn Monroe.

title: Boy Erased
description: The son of a Baptist preacher unwillingly participates in a church-supported gay conversion program after being forcibly outed to his parents.

title: The Iceman
description: The story of Richard Kuklinski, the notorious contract killer and family man. When finally arrested in 1986, neither his wife nor daughters had any clue about his real profession.

title: Kaze tachinu
description: A look at the life of Jiro Horikoshi, the man who designed Japanese fighter planes during World War II.

title: Florence Foster Jenkins
description: The story of Florence Foster Jenkins, a New York heiress who dreamed of becoming an opera singer, despite having a terrible singing voice.

title: Bully
description: A pack of naïve teenagers conspire to murder a mutual friend, whose aggressive demeanor has proved too much.

title: Girl with a Pearl Earring
description: A young peasant maid working in the house of painter Johannes Vermeer becomes his talented assistant and the model for one of his most famous works.

title: Julie & Julia
description: Julia Child's story of her start in the cooking profession is intertwined with blogger Julie Powell's 2002 challenge to cook all the recipes in Child's first book.

title: An American Crime
description: The true story of suburban housewife Gertrude Baniszewski, who kept a teenage girl locked in the basement of her Indiana home during the 1960s.

title: The Egyptian
description: In ancient Egypt, a poor orphan becomes a genial physician and is eventually appointed at the Pharaoh's court where he witnesses palace intrigues and learns dangerous royal secrets.

title: Rudy
description: Rudy has always been told that he was too small to play college football. But he is determined to overcome the odds and fulfill his dream of playing for Notre Dame.

title: Good Morning, Vietnam
description: In 1965, an unorthodox and irreverent DJ named Adrian Cronauer begins to shake up things when he is assigned to the U.S. Armed Services radio station in Vietnam.

title: Allen v. Farrow
description: A look behind the years of sensational headlines to reveal the private story of the accusation of sexual abuse against Woody Allen involving his 7-year-old daughter with Mia Farrow.

title: Shirley
description: A famous horror writer finds inspiration for her next book after she and her husband take in a young couple.

title: Saving Mr. Banks
description: Author P.L. Travers reflects on her childhood after reluctantly meeting with Walt Disney, who seeks to adapt her Mary Poppins books for the big screen.

title: October Sky
description: The true story of Homer Hickam, a coal miner's son who was inspired by the first Sputnik launch to take up rocketry against his father's wishes.

title: Patton
description: The World War II phase of the career of controversial American general George S. Patton.

title: Finding Neverland
description: The story of Sir J.M. Barrie's friendship with a family who inspired him to create Peter Pan.

title: Elizabeth
description: The early years of the reign of Elizabeth I of England and her difficult task of learning what is necessary to be a monarch.

title: The Great Ziegfeld
description: The ups and downs of Florenz Ziegfeld Jr., famed producer of extravagant stage revues, are portrayed.

title: Milk
description: The story of Harvey Milk and his struggles as an American gay activist who fought for gay rights and became California's first openly gay elected official.

title: Bloodsport
description: "Bloodsport" follows Frank Dux, an American martial artist serving in the military, who decides to leave the army to compete in a martial arts tournament in Hong Kong where fights to the death can occur.

title: Sixty Six
description: A boy's barmitzvah looks set to be a disaster when it coincides with the 1966 World Cup Final.

title: Saina
description: The story of Saina Nehwal, a professional badminton player who ranked number 1 in the sport.

title: Audrey
description: Filmmaker Helena Coan examines the remarkable life and career of actress, fashion icon and humanitarian Audrey Hepburn.

title: Seberg
description: Inspired by real events in the life of French New Wave icon Jean Seberg. In the late 1960s, Hoover's FBI targeted her because of her political and romantic involvement with civil rights activist Hakim Jamal.

title: La Bamba
description: Biographical story of the rise from nowhere of early rock and roll singer Ritchie Valens who died at age 17 in a plane crash with Buddy Holly and The Big Bopper.

title: Confessions of a Dangerous Mind
description: An adaptation of the cult memoir of game show impresario Chuck Barris (Sam Rockwell), in which he purports to have been a C.I.A. hitman.

title: The Zookeeper's Wife
description: Keepers of the Warsaw Zoo, Antonina and Jan Zabinski, must save hundreds of people and animals during the Nazi invasion in WWII Poland.

title: The Devils
description: In 17th-century France, Father Urbain Grandier seeks to protect the city of Loudun from the corrupt establishment of Cardinal Richelieu. Hysteria occurs within the city when he is accused of witchcraft by a sexually repressed nun.

title: The Long Riders
description: The origins, exploits and the ultimate fate of the Jesse James gang is told in a sympathetic portrayal of the bank robbers made up of brothers who begin their legendary bank raids because of revenge.

title: Lovelace
description: The story of Linda Lovelace, who is used and abused by the porn industry at the behest of her coercive husband before taking control of her life.

title: The Young Victoria
description: A dramatization of the turbulent first years of Queen Victoria's rule, and her enduring romance with Prince Albert.

title: Big Eyes
description: A drama about the awakening of painter Margaret Keane, her phenomenal success in the 1950s, and the subsequent legal difficulties she had with her husband, who claimed credit for her works in the 1960s.

title: A Very English Scandal
description: British Liberal Party leader Jeremy Thorpe is accused of conspiracy to murder his gay ex-lover and forced to stand trial in 1979.

title: Roots
description: An adaptation of Alex Haley's "Roots", chronicling the history of an African man sold to slavery in America, and his descendants.

title: Yip Man
description: During the Japanese invasion of China, a wealthy martial artist is forced to leave his home when his city is occupied. With little means of providing for themselves, Ip Man and the remaining members of the city must find a way to survive.

title: Hemingway & Gellhorn
description: A drama centered on the romance between Ernest Hemingway and World War II correspondent Martha Gellhorn, Hemingway's inspiration for For Whom the Bell Tolls, and the only woman who ever asked for a divorce from the writer.

title: Selma
description: A chronicle of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.'s campaign to secure equal voting rights via an epic march from Selma to Montgomery, Alabama, in 1965.

title: Lords of Chaos
description: A teenager's quest to launch Norwegian Black Metal in Oslo in the early 1990s results in a very violent outcome.

title: Charlie Wilson's War
description: A drama based on a Texas congressman Charlie Wilson's covert dealings in Afghanistan, where his efforts to assist rebels in their war with the Soviets have some unforeseen and long-reaching effects.

title: Men of Honor
description: The story of Carl Brashear, the first African-American U.S. Navy Diver, and the man who trained him.

title: Trumbo
description: In 1947, Dalton Trumbo was Hollywood's top screenwriter, until he and other artists were jailed and blacklisted for their political beliefs.

title: The New World
description: The story of the English exploration of Virginia, and of the changing world and loves of Pocahontas.

title: A Dangerous Method
description: A look at how the intense relationship between Carl Jung and Sigmund Freud gives birth to psychoanalysis.

title: The 15:17 to Paris
description: An attempted terrorist attack on a Paris bound train is prevented by three courageous young Americans. Their friendship was their greatest weapon that saved the lives of those on board.

title: Pam & Tommy
description: Follows the story of their relationship going back to their whirlwind romance that started with them marrying after only knowing each other for 96 hours in 1995.

title: My Left Foot: The Story of Christy Brown
description: Christy Brown, born with cerebral palsy, learns to paint and write with his only controllable limb - his left foot.

title: Temple Grandin
description: A biopic of Temple Grandin, an autistic woman who has become one of the top scientists in the humane livestock handling industry.

title: Cinderella Man
description: The story of James J. Braddock, a supposedly washed-up boxer who came back to challenge for the heavyweight championship of the world.

title: I Saw the Light
description: The story of the country-western singer Hank Williams, who in his brief life created one of the greatest bodies of work in American music. The film chronicles his rise to fame and its tragic effect on his health and personal life.

title: Jobs
description: The story of Steve Jobs' ascension from college dropout into one of the most revered creative entrepreneurs of the 20th century.

title: Chariots of Fire
description: Two British track athletes, one a determined Jew, and the other a devout Christian, compete in the 1924 Olympics.

title: Good Joe Bell
description: The true story of a small town, working class father who embarks on a solo walk across the U.S. to crusade against bullying after his son is tormented in high school for being gay.

title: The Runaways
description: A coming-of-age biographical film about the 1970s teenage all-girl rock band The Runaways. The relationship between band members Cherie Currie and Joan Jett is also explored.

title: Kill Your Darlings
description: A murder in 1944 draws together the great poets of the beat generation: Allen Ginsberg, Jack Kerouac, and William Burroughs.

title: Werk ohne Autor
description: German artist Kurt Barnert has escaped East Germany and now lives in West Germany, but is tormented by his childhood under the Nazis and the GDR-regime.

title: Heaven Is for Real
description: A small-town father must find the courage and conviction to share his son's extraordinary, life-changing experience with the world.

title: Kon-Tiki
description: Legendary explorer Thor Heyerdahl's epic 4,300-mile crossing of the Pacific on a balsawood raft in 1947, in an effort to prove that it was possible for South Americans to settle in Polynesia in pre-Columbian times.

title: Funny Girl
description: The life of Fanny Brice, famed comedienne and entertainer of the early 1900s. We see her rise to fame as a Ziegfeld girl, subsequent career, and her personal life, particularly her relationship with Nick Arnstein.

title: The Duchess
description: A chronicle of the life of 18th-century aristocrat Georgiana, Duchess of Devonshire, who was reviled for her extravagant political and personal life.

title: This Boy's Life
description: The story about the relationship between a rebellious 1950s teenager and his abusive stepfather, based on the memoirs of writer and literature Professor Tobias Wolff.

title: Zerkalo
description: A dying man in his forties remembers his past. His childhood, his mother, the war, personal moments and things that tell of the recent history of all the Russian nation.

title: Battle of the Sexes
description: The true story of the 1973 tennis match between World number one Billie Jean King and ex-champ and serial hustler Bobby Riggs.

title: Fosse/Verdon
description: An inside look at the romantic and creative partnership between influential choreographer/director, Bob Fosse, and Gwen Verdon, one of the greatest Broadway dancers of all time.

title: The Killing Fields
description: A journalist is trapped in Cambodia during tyrant Pol Pot's bloody 'Year Zero' cleansing campaign, which claimed the lives of two million 'undesirable' civilians.

title: Breathe
description: The inspiring true love story of Robin (Andrew Garfield) and Diana Cavendish (Claire Foy), an adventurous couple who refuse to give up in the face of a devastating disease. Their heartwarming celebration of human possibility marks the directorial debut of Andy Serkis.

title: J. Edgar
description: J. Edgar Hoover, powerful head of the F.B.I. for nearly fifty years, looks back on his professional and personal life.

title: Kill the Irishman
description: The true story of Danny Greene, a tough Irish thug working for mobsters in Cleveland during the 1970's.

title: Concussion
description: In Pittsburgh, accomplished pathologist Dr. Bennet Omalu uncovers the truth about brain damage in football players who suffer repeated concussions in the course of normal play.

title: Stan & Ollie
description: Laurel and Hardy, the world's most famous comedy duo, attempt to reignite their film careers as they embark on what becomes their swan song - a grueling theatre tour of post-war Britain.

title: Hunger
description: Irish republican Bobby Sands leads the inmates of a Northern Irish prison in a hunger strike.

title: Billionaire Boys Club
description: A group of wealthy boys in Los Angeles during the early 1980s establish a 'get-rich-quick' scam that turns deadly.

title: Bigger
description: The inspirational tale of the grandfathers of fitness as we now know it, Joe and Ben Weider. Facing anti-Semitism and extreme poverty, the brothers beat all odds to build an empire and inspire future generations.

title: I'm Not There
description: Ruminations on the life of Bob Dylan, where six characters embody a different aspect of the musician's life and work.

title: Being the Ricardos
description: Follows Lucy and Desi as they face a crisis that could end their careers and another that could end their marriage.

title: Born on the Fourth of July
description: The biography of Ron Kovic. Paralyzed in the Vietnam war, he becomes an anti-war and pro-human rights political activist after feeling betrayed by the country he fought for.

title: Veneno
description: A biographical story of La Veneno, transgender icon and TV personality, and those who surrounded her.

title: Patch Adams
description: The true story of a heroic man, Hunter "Patch" Adams, determined to become a medical doctor because he enjoys helping people. He ventured where no doctor had ventured before, using humour and pathos.

title: The Libertine
description: The story of John Wilmot, a.k.a. the Earl of Rochester, a 17th century poet who famously drank and debauched his way to an early grave, only to earn posthumous critical acclaim for his life's work.

title: Three Identical Strangers
description: In 1980 New York, three young men who were all adopted meet each other and find out they're triplets who were separated at birth. But their quest to find out why turns into a bizarre and sinister mystery.

title: Paul, Apostle of Christ
description: Luke travels Roma looking for apostle Paul, turned in Nero's prisoner, to tell his story before his execution.

title: Fruitvale Station
description: The story of Oscar Grant III, a 22-year-old Bay Area resident, who crosses paths with friends, enemies, family, and strangers on the last day of 2008.

title: Henry: Portrait of a Serial Killer
description: Arriving in Chicago, Henry 'Michael Rooker, in what is undoubtedly the finest performance of his patchy career', moves in with ex-con acquaintance Otis and starts schooling him in the ways of the serial killer.

title: Anthropoid
description: Based on the extraordinary true story of Operation Anthropoid, the WWII mission to assassinate SS General Reinhard Heydrich, the main architect behind the Final Solution and the Reich's third in command after Hitler and Himmler.

title: The Straight Story
description: An old man makes a long journey by lawnmower to mend his relationship with an ill brother.

title: Respect
description: The life story of legendary R&B singer, Aretha Franklin.

title: Sergio
description: A sweeping drama set in the chaotic aftermath of the US invasion of Iraq, where the life of top UN diplomat Sergio Vieira de Mello hangs in the balance during the most treacherous mission of his career.

title: Billie Eilish: The World's a Little Blurry
description: An intimate look at the singer-songwriter's journey, navigating life on the road, on stage, and at home, while creating her debut album.

title: Goodbye Christopher Robin
description: The relationship between writer AA Milne and his son, Christopher Robin, and how this became the inspiration for Winnie the Pooh.

title: My Friend Dahmer
description: A young Jeffrey Dahmer struggles to belong in high school.

title: Feud
description: Planned anthology series centering on famous feuds, including Bette Davis and Joan Crawford that is discontinued at the moment.

title: Pride
description: U.K. gay activists work to help miners during their lengthy strike of the National Union of Mineworkers in the summer of 1984.

title: HHhH
description: As the German Fascists expand their borders, scorching Europe from end to end, two brave Czechs of the Resistance prepare for a suicide mission to assassinate Reinhard Heydrich, the hideous mastermind behind the "Final Solution".

title: Hitchcock
description: The relationship between Alfred Hitchcock and his wife Alma Reville during the filming of Psycho (1960) in 1959 is explored.

title: Dangerous Minds
description: An ex-Marine turned teacher struggles to connect with her students in an inner city school.

title: Agora
description: A historical drama set in Roman Egypt, concerning a slave who turns to the rising tide of Christianity in the hope of pursuing freedom while falling in love with his mistress, the philosophy and mathematics professor Hypatia of Alexandria.

title: Driven
description: Intense thriller where politics, big business and narcotics collide.

title: Miss Potter
description: The story of Beatrix Potter, the author of the beloved and best-selling children's book, "The Tale of Peter Rabbit", and her struggle for love, happiness, and success.

title: Mr. Jones
description: A Welsh journalist breaks the news in the western media of the famine in Ukraine in the early 1930s.

title: A Private War
description: One of the most celebrated war correspondents of our time, Marie Colvin is an utterly fearless and rebellious spirit, driven to the frontline of conflicts across the globe to give voice to the voiceless.

title: Love & Mercy
description: In the 60s, Beach Boys leader Brian Wilson struggles with emerging psychosis as he attempts to craft his avant-garde pop masterpiece. In the 80s, he is a broken, confused man under the 24-hour watch of shady therapist Dr. Eugene Landy.

title: The Iron Lady
description: An elderly Margaret Thatcher talks to the imagined presence of her recently deceased husband as she struggles to come to terms with his death while scenes from her past life, from girlhood to British prime minister, intervene.

title: Loving Vincent
description: In a story depicted in oil painted animation, a young man comes to the last hometown of painter Vincent van Gogh (Robert Gulaczyk) to deliver the troubled artist's final letter and ends up investigating his final days there.

title: Skin
description: A destitute young man, raised by racist skinheads and notorious among white supremacists, turns his back on hatred and violence to transform his life, with the help of a black activist and the woman he loves.

title: My Week with Marilyn
description: Colin Clark, an employee of Sir Laurence Olivier, documents the tense interaction between Olivier and Marilyn Monroe during the production of The Prince and the Showgirl (1957).

title: Escape from Alcatraz
description: Alcatraz is the most secure prison of its time. It is believed that no one can ever escape from it, until three daring men make a possible successful attempt at escaping from one of the most infamous prisons in the world.

title: Aquarius
description: A gritty 1960s cop drama about LAPD detective Sam Hodiak and his trainee, who must deal with gangs, brutal crimes, changing times, family crises and unhinged manipulative small-time crook Charles Manson, who's slowly building his cult.

title: Don't Worry, He Won't Get Far on Foot
description: On the rocky path to sobriety after a life-changing accident, John Callahan discovers the healing power of art, willing his injured hands into drawing hilarious, often controversial cartoons, which bring him a new lease on life.

title: Andrei Rublev
description: The life, times and afflictions of the fifteenth-century Russian iconographer St. Andrei Rublev.

title: Private Parts
description: The autobiographical story of Howard Stern, the radio rebel who is now also a TV personality, an author and a movie star.

title: True Story
description: When disgraced New York Times reporter Michael Finkel meets accused killer Christian Longo - who has taken on Finkel's identity - his investigation morphs into a game of cat-and-mouse.

title: Sid and Nancy
description: The relationship between Sid Vicious, bassist for British punk group Sex Pistols, and his girlfriend Nancy Spungen is portrayed.

title: Same Kind of Different as Me
description: International art dealer Ron Hall must befriend a dangerous homeless man in order to save his struggling marriage to his wife, a woman whose dreams will lead all three of them on the journey of their lives.

title: Eddie the Eagle
description: The story of Eddie Edwards, the notoriously tenacious British underdog ski jumper who charmed the world at the 1988 Winter Olympics.

title: Tick, Tick... Boom
description: The story of Jon, an aspiring theater composer who is waiting tables in New York City while writing Superbia - which he hopes will be the next great American musical and finally give him his big break.

title: The People vs. Larry Flynt
description: The story of controversial pornography publisher Larry Flynt, and how he became a defender of free speech.

title: The Glorias
description: The story of feminist icon Gloria Steinem's itinerant childhood and its influence on her life as a writer, activist and organizer for women's rights worldwide.

title: All Eyez on Me
description: Tells the true and untold story of prolific rapper, actor, poet and activist Tupac Shakur.

title: Tracks
description: A young woman goes on a 1,700-mile trek across the deserts of West Australia with four camels and her faithful dog.

title: Jackie
description: Following the assassination of President John F. Kennedy, First Lady Jacqueline Kennedy fights through grief and trauma to regain her faith, console her children, and define her husband's historic legacy.

title: Christiane F. - Wir Kinder vom Bahnhof Zoo
description: A teen girl in 1970's Berlin becomes addicted to heroin. Everything in her life slowly begins to distort and disappear as she befriends a small crew of junkies and falls in love with a drug-abusing male prostitute.

title: The King and I
description: A widow accepts a job as a live-in governess to the King of Siam's children.

title: Man on the Moon
description: The life and career of legendary comedian Andy Kaufman.

title: En kongelig affære
description: A young queen, who is married to an insane king, falls secretly in love with her physician - and together they start a revolution that changes a nation forever.

title: Fire in the Sky
description: An Arizona logger mysteriously disappears for five days in an alleged encounter with a flying saucer in 1975. His co-workers endure ridicule and contempt as they are wrongly accused of murder.

title: Invincible
description: Based on the story of Vince Papale, a 30-year-old bartender from South Philadelphia who overcame long odds to play for the NFL's Philadelphia Eagles in 1976.

title: A Futile and Stupid Gesture
description: In the 1970s and '80s, National Lampoon's success and influence creates a new media empire overseen in part by the brilliant and troubled Douglas Kenney.

title: Quo Vadis
description: Fierce Roman commander Marcus Vinicius becomes infatuated with beautiful Christian hostage Lygia and begins questioning the tyrannical leadership of the despot Emperor Nero.

title: The Sapphires
description: It's 1968, and four young, talented Australian Aboriginal girls learn about love, friendship and war when their all-girl group The Sapphires entertain the US troops in Vietnam.

title: Brexit: The Uncivil War
description: Political strategist Dominic Cummings leads a popular but controversial campaign to convince British voters to leave the European Union from 2015 up until the present day.

title: Hidalgo
description: In 1890, a down-and-out cowboy and his horse travel to Arabia to compete in a deadly cross desert horse race.

title: Belle
description: The mixed-race daughter, Dido Elizabeth Belle (Gugu Mbatha-Raw), of Royal Navy Captain Sir John Lindsay (Matthew Goode) is raised by aristocratic Great-uncle Lord William Murray, 1st Earl of Mansfield (Tom Wilkinson) in eighteenth century England.

title: King of Thieves
description: A true crime movie about a crew of retired crooks who pull off a major heist in London's jewelry district. What starts off as their last criminal hurrah, quickly turns into a brutal nightmare due to greed. Based on infamous true events.

title: El robo del siglo
description: In 2006, a group of thieves performed what is considered one of the most famous and smart bank heists in the history of Argentina when they rob the Banco Río branch in Acassuso.

title: Pawn Sacrifice
description: Set during the Cold War, American chess prodigy Bobby Fischer finds himself caught between two superpowers and his own struggles as he challenges the Soviet Empire.

title: Elizabeth: The Golden Age
description: A mature Queen Elizabeth endures multiple crises late in her reign including court intrigues, an assassination plot, the Spanish Armada, and romantic disappointments.

title: Glory Road
description: In 1966, Texas Western coach Don Haskins led the first all-black starting line-up for a college basketball team to the NCAA national championship.

title: Notorious
description: The life and death story of The Notorious B.I.G. (a.k.a. Christopher Wallace), who came straight out of Brooklyn to take the world of rap music by storm.

title: Bugsy
description: The story of how Benjamin "Bugsy" Siegel started Las Vegas.

title: Domino
description: A recounting of Domino Harvey's life story. The daughter of actor Laurence Harvey turned away from her career as a Ford model to become a bounty hunter.

title: Burden
description: When a museum celebrating the Ku Klux Klan opens in a South Carolina town, the idealistic Reverend Kennedy strives to keep the peace even as he urges the group's Grand Dragon to disavow his racist past.

title: Pablo Escobar: El Patrón del Mal
description: The exploits of the notorious drug lord, Pablo Escobar.

title: David Attenborough: A Life on Our Planet
description: One man has seen more of the natural world than any other. This unique feature documentary is his witness statement.

title: Pretend It's a City
description: Wander the New York City streets and fascinating mind of wry writer, humorist and raconteur Fran Lebowitz as she sits down with Martin Scorsese.

title: Yi dai zong shi
description: The story of martial-arts master Ip Man, the man who trained Bruce Lee.

title: Kill the Messenger
description: Journalist Gary Webb, California 1996, started investigating CIA's role in the 1980s in getting crack cocaine to the black part of LA to get money and weapons to the Contras/freedom fighters in Nicaragua.

title: The Old Man & the Gun
description: Based on the true story of Forrest Tucker and his audacious escape from San Quentin at the age of 70 to an unprecedented string of heists that confounded authorities and enchanted the public.

title: Winchester
description: Ensconced in her sprawling San Jose, California mansion, eccentric firearm heiress Sarah Winchester (Dame Helen Mirren) believes she is haunted by the souls of people killed by the Winchester repeating rifle.

title: 24 Hour Party People
description: In 1976, Tony Wilson sets up Factory Records and brings Manchester's music to the world.

title: Quills
description: In a Napoleonic era insane asylum, an inmate, the irrepressible Marquis De Sade, fights a battle of wills against a tyrannically prudish doctor.

title: Woman Walks Ahead
description: Catherine Weldon, a portrait painter from 1890s Brooklyn, travels to Dakota to paint a portrait of Sitting Bull and becomes embroiled in the Lakota peoples' struggle over the rights to their land.

title: Marshall
description: The story of Thurgood Marshall, the crusading lawyer who would become the first African-American Supreme Court Justice, as he battles through one of his career-defining cases.

title: A Man for All Seasons
description: The story of Sir Thomas More, who stood up to King Henry VIII when the King rejected the Roman Catholic Church to obtain a divorce and remarry.

title: From Straight A's to XXX
description: In order to pay her college tuition, a young woman turns to the adult film industry and must balance her personal life with a new life as porn star Belle Knox.

title: The Express
description: A drama based on the life of college football hero Ernie Davis, the first African-American to win the Heisman Trophy.

title: The Eyes of Tammy Faye
description: An intimate look at the extraordinary rise, fall and redemption of televangelist Tammy Faye Bakker.

title: Chasing Mavericks
description: When young Jay Moriarity discovers that the mythic Mavericks surf break, one of the biggest waves on Earth, exists just miles from his Santa Cruz home, he enlists the help of local legend Frosty Hesson to train him to survive it.

title: The Ten Commandments
description: After hearing the story of Moses, the sons of a devout Christian mother go their own ways, while the atheist brother's breaking of the Ten Commandments leads to tragedy.

title: Mommie Dearest
description: The abusive and traumatic adoptive upbringing of Christina Crawford at the hands of her mother, screen queen Joan Crawford, is depicted.

title: Le scaphandre et le papillon
description: The true story of Elle editor Jean-Dominique Bauby who suffers a stroke and has to live with an almost totally paralyzed body; only his left eye isn't paralyzed.

title: The Kid
description: The story of a young boy who witnesses Billy the Kid's encounter with Sheriff Pat Garrett.

title: Borgia
description: Story of the rise and the fall of the Renaissance dynasty.

title: The Mercy
description: The incredible story of amateur sailor Donald Crowhurst and his solo attempt to circumnavigate the globe. The struggles he confronted on the journey while his family awaited his return is one of the most enduring mysteries of recent times.

title: Loving
description: The story of Richard and Mildred Loving, a couple whose arrest for interracial marriage in 1960s Virginia began a legal battle that would end with the Supreme Court's historic 1967 decision.

description: The story of T.E. Lawrence, the English officer who successfully united and led the diverse, often warring, Arab tribes during World War I in order to fight the Turks.

title: Lincoln
description: As the American Civil War continues to rage, America's president struggles with continuing carnage on the battlefield as he fights with many inside his own cabinet on the decision to emancipate the slaves.

title: Versailles
description: In 1667, 28-year-old all-powerful king of France, Louis XIV, decides to build the greatest palace in the world - Versailles. But drained budget, affairs and political intrigues complicate things.

title: Robin Hood

title: Outlaw King
description: A true David vs. Goliath story of how the 14th century Scottish 'Outlaw King' Robert the Bruce used cunning and bravery to defeat the much larger and better equipped occupying English army.

title: The Spanish Princess
description: The beautiful Spanish princess, Catherine of Aragon, navigates the royal lineage of England with an eye on the throne.

title: Des

title: The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas
description: Through the innocent eyes of Bruno, the eight-year-old son of the commandant at a German concentration camp, a forbidden friendship with a Jewish boy on the other side of the camp fence has startling and unexpected consequences.

title: The Last Dance

title: Hatfields & McCoys
description: Dramatization of the bitter blood feud between the two families on the West Virginia/Kentucky border in the years after the Civil War.

title: Marco Polo

title: Misbehaviour

title: Spartacus
description: The slave Spartacus leads a violent revolt against the decadent Roman Republic.

title: Kid 90

title: Deepwater Horizon

title: Spencer

title: TURN
description: A Long Island farmer bands together a group of childhood friends to form an unlikely group of spies who turn the tide in America's fight for independence.

title: King of Kings
description: The temporary physical life of the Biblical Savior, Jesus Christ.

title: Judy
description: Legendary performer Judy Garland arrives in London in the winter of 1968 to perform a series of sold-out concerts.

title: Munich
description: Based on the true story of the Black September aftermath, about the five men chosen to eliminate the ones responsible for that fateful day.

title: Kurulus: Osman
description: The series will focus on the life of Osman Bey, the son of Ertugrul Gazi and the founder of the Ottoman Empire.

title: In the Heart of the Sea
description: A recounting of a New England whaling ship's sinking by a giant whale in 1820, an experience that later inspired the great novel Moby-Dick.

title: The Three Musketeers
description: The hot-headed young D'Artagnan along with three former legendary but now down on their luck Musketeers must unite and defeat a beautiful double agent and her villainous employer from seizing the French throne and engulfing Europe in war.

title: The Spy

title: The Great Escape

title: Cleopatra

title: Frontier

title: Woman in Gold

title: Operation Finale

title: The 13th Warrior
description: A man, having fallen in love with the wrong woman, is sent by the sultan himself on a diplomatic mission to a distant land as an ambassador. Stopping at a Viking village port to restock on supplies, he finds himself unwittingly embroiled in a quest to banish a mysterious threat in a distant Viking land.

title: Empire of the Sun
description: A young English boy struggles to survive under Japanese occupation of China during World War II.

title: Colonia

title: Barry Lyndon

title: The Longest Day

title: Enemy at the Gates
description: A Russian and a German sniper play a game of cat-and-mouse during the Battle of Stalingrad.

title: Robert the Bruce
description: The story of the nobleman-turned-outlaw hero who was crowned king of Scots in the 14th century.

title: The Laundromat

title: The Eagle

title: Roman Empire
description: Chronicles some of the most famous leaders of the Roman Civilization.

description: The dramatic story of the cutthroat race between electricity titans Thomas A. Edison and George Westinghouse to determine whose electrical system would power the modern world.

description: High-stakes exploits turn deadly - and shake a global church to its core - in the extraordinary true crime story.
"21" is the fact-based story about six MIT students who were trained to become experts in card counting and subsequently took Vegas casinos for millions in winnings.

title: The Way Back
description: Siberian gulag escapees travel four thousand miles by foot to freedom in India.

title: The Catcher Was a Spy

title: Spartacus: Gods of the Arena
description: In the time before the arrival of Spartacus, the House of Batiatus faces many challenges from competitors, and within its own household.

description: During World War II era, a young woman, Wang Jiazhi, gets swept up in a dangerous game of emotional intrigue with a powerful political figure, Mr. Yee.

description: The Kung Fu master travels to the U.S. where his student has upset the local martial arts community by opening a Wing Chun school.

description: Historical reenactments by A-list talent are presented by inebriated storytellers.

title: Den 12. mann
description: They were 12 saboteurs. The Nazis killed 11 of them. This is the true story of the one who got away...

description: The life story of Jesus is told from his humble birth through his teachings, crucifixion and ultimate resurrection.

title: The Last Emperor
description: The story of the final Emperor of China.

description: Two friends, one northern and one southern, struggle to maintain their friendship as events build towards the American Civil War.

title: Hotel Mumbai

title: Rob Roy

title: Roots
description: A dramatization of author Alex Haley's family line from ancestor Kunta Kinte's enslavement to his descendants' liberation.

title: Entebbe

title: The Frankenstein Chronicles

title: The Mission

title: Child 44

title: Kaze tachinu

title: Pan Am

title: Miseuteo Shunshain

title: The Egyptian

title: Centurion

title: Cool Runnings
description: When a Jamaican sprinter is disqualified from the Olympic Games, he enlists the help of a dishonored coach to start the first Jamaican Bobsled Team.

title: Elizabeth
description: The early years of the reign of Elizabeth I of England and her difficult task of learning what is necessary to be a monarch.

title: The Food That Built America

title: The Devils
description: In 17th-century France, Father Urbain Grandier seeks to protect the city of Loudun from the corrupt establishment of Cardinal Richelieu. Hysteria occurs within the city when he is accused of witchcraft by a sexually repressed nun.

title: The Young Victoria
description: A dramatization of the turbulent first years of Queen Victoria's rule, and her enduring romance with Prince Albert.

title: The Vietnam War
description: A comprehensive history of the United States' involvement in the bitterly divisive armed conflict in Southeast Asia.

title: Zimna wojna
description: In the 1950s, a music director falls in love with a singer and tries to persuade her to flee communist Poland for France.

title: A Very English Scandal
description: British Liberal Party leader Jeremy Thorpe is accused of conspiracy to murder his gay ex-lover and forced to stand trial in 1979.

title: Roots
description: An adaptation of Alex Haley's "Roots", chronicling the history of an African man sold to slavery in America, and his descendants.

title: Yip Man

title: The New World

title: Under sandet

title: Jamestown

title: The Duchess

title: The Killing Fields

title: Ying xiong
description: A defense officer, Nameless, was summoned by the King of Qin regarding his success of terminating three warriors.

title: The Way of the Wind
description: A retelling of several episodes in the life of the Christ.

title: The Tragedy of Macbeth

title: The Hero

description: Head back to Lonesome Dove in this sequel to one of the most-loved miniseries of all time.

title: Bad Day at Black Rock
description: A one-armed stranger comes to a tiny town possessing a terrible past they want to keep secret, by violent means if necessary.

description: After the Civil War, Cord McNally searches for the traitor whose treachery caused the defeat of McNally's unit and the loss of a close friend.

title: Out of the Wild
description: Out of the Wild is the story of Henry McBride, a down and out cowboy with a painful past he can't drink away. Living on his last dollar with nowhere to go, he ends up working the last place...                See full summary »

description: Plot kept under wraps. Third installment of the 'Young Guns' film franchise.

title: The Harder They Fall
description: When an outlaw discovers his enemy is being released from prison, he reunites his gang to seek revenge in this Western.

description: The story of how the Texas Rangers were created.

description: In 1872, an embittered gunslinger named John Henry Clayton attempts to make amends with his estranged father Reverend Samuel Clayton while their community is besieged by ruthless land-grabbers.

title: Streets of Laredo
description: Captain Woodrow Call, now retired from the Rangers, is a bounty hunter. He is hired by an eastern rail baron to track down Joey Garza, a new kind of killer, only a boy, who kills from a ...                See full summary »

description: The adventures of the masked hero and his Native American partner.

title: Lancer
description: Western in the similar to " The Big Valley, Bonanza, The High Chaparral " about the Lancer family and its ranch.

title: Ned Kelly
description: An innocent man becomes one of the most wanted criminals the world has ever known.

description: Western legends Pat Garrett, Doc Holliday and Billy the Kid are played against each other over the law and the attentions of vivacious country vixen Rio McDonald.

title: Bad Girls
description: Four prostitutes join together to travel the Old West.

title: Wanted: Dead or Alive

title: Hang 'Em High
description: When an innocent man barely survives a lynching, he returns as a lawman determined to bring the vigilantes to justice.

description: The neighbors of a frontier family turn on them when it is suspected that their adopted daughter was stolen from the local Kiowa tribe.

title: The Proposition
description: A lawman apprehends a notorious outlaw and gives him nine days to kill his older brother, or else they'll execute his younger brother.

title: The Last Hard Men

title: Broken Arrow

title: The Sons of Katie Elder
description: Ranch owner Katie Elder's four sons determine to avenge the murder of their father and the swindling of their mother.

title: Carry On Cowboy
description: Stodge City is in the grip of the Rumpo Kid and his gang. Mistaken identity again takes a hand as a "sanitary engineer" (plumber) by the name of Marshal P. Knutt is mistaken for a law marshal! Being the conscientious sort, Marshal tries to help the town get rid of Rumpo, and a showdown is inevitable. Marshal has two aids - revenge-seeking Annie Oakley and his sanitary expertise...

title: The Warrant
description: After fighting in the Civil War, two Union Army buddies find themselves on opposite sides of the law with the post-war peace at risk.

title: The Naked Spur
description: A bounty hunter trying to bring a murderer to justice is forced to accept the help of two less-than-trustworthy strangers.

title: Red River

title: In a Valley of Violence
description: A mysterious stranger and a random act of violence drag a town of misfits and nitwits into the bloody crosshairs of revenge.

title: The Man from Snowy River

title: Hondo

title: Home on the Range

title: Column South
description: Before the Civil War, Lt. Jed Sayre's efforts to conciliate the cavalry and the Navajo are undermined by his racist C.O. and Confederate sympathizers.

title: The Scalphunters

title: The Warrior's Way
description: A warrior-assassin is forced to hide in a small town in the American Badlands after refusing a mission.

title: The Adventures of Brisco County, Jr.
description: A bounty hunter rides the Old West, fighting bad guys, many with futuristic-type gadgets.

title: Gunfight at the O.K. Corral
description: Lawman Wyatt Earp and outlaw Doc Holliday form an unlikely alliance which culminates in their participation in the legendary Gunfight at the O.K. Corral.

title: Jane Got a Gun
description: A woman asks her ex-lover for help in order to save her outlaw husband from a gang out to kill him.

title: Paint Your Wagon
description: Two unlikely prospector partners share the same wife in a California gold rush mining town.

title: Seraphim Falls
description: At the end of the Civil War, a colonel hunts down a man with whom he has a grudge.

title: Ride Lonesome
description: A bounty hunter escorts a killer to be tried for murder, but allows the man's outlaw brother to catch up with them to have a showdown over a previous shocking murder.

title: Pure Country

title: Texas Across the River
description: In 1845 Texas, a Louisiana belle is courted by a wanted Spanish nobleman and a Texas brawling gunrunner but her suitors' passionate duel is interrupted by the cavalry and a Comanche attack.

title: Tyger Tyger
description: After robbing a pharmacy, a selfless woman and her mute friend kidnap a drug addict then hit the road to distribute the stolen "life saving" medication, but find themselves trapped in the fringe lands of a law-less and psychedelic city.

description: Revisionist western about fallen preacher Shay, who guns down his wife Raysha for running off with another man. Wandering, he meets single mom Laurie. However, helpless sheriff Scoby wants Shay to help him fight the villainous Clavers.

title: The Shooting
description: A mysterious woman persuades two cowboys to help her in a revenge scheme.

title: Spirit Riding Free
description: The wild west adventures of a free-spirited girl and her wild stallion horse companion.

title: Zorro
description: Don Diego de la Vega opposes the corrupt tyrants of Spanish California as the masked swordsman, Zorro.

title: Joheunnom nabbeunnom isanghannom
description: The story of two outlaws and a bounty hunter in 1940s Manchuria and their rivalry to possess a treasure map while being pursued by the Japanese army and Chinese bandits.

title: Hangman's Knot
description: A Confederate Major and his troops are falsely led to believe the Civil War is not over, and become wanted men after they attack a Union Army wagon train in Nevada.

title: Alias Smith and Jones
description: Hannibal Heyes and Kid Curry, two of the most wanted outlaws in the history of the West, are popular "with everyone except the railroads and the banks".

title: Bounty Law
description: The story of Jake Cahill.

title: Badland
description: Detective Matthias Breecher is hired to track down the worst of the Confederate war criminals. As he roams the Old West seeking justice, his resolve is tested when he meets a determined pioneer woman who is far more than she seems.

title: Billy Jack
description: Ex-Green Beret hapkido expert saves wild horses from being slaughtered for dog food and helps protect a desert "freedom school" for runaway.

title: Tom and Huck
description: Two best friends witness a murder and embark on a series of adventures in order to prove the innocence of the man wrongly accused of the crime.

title: Wild Bill
description: The early career of legendary lawman Wild Bill Hickock is telescoped and culminates in his relocation in Deadwood and a reunion with Calamity Jane.

title: Almost Heroes

title: How the West Was Won
description: The Macahans, a family from Virginia, headed by Zeb Macahan, travel across the country to pioneer a new land and a new home in the American West.

title: Y: 1883
description: Follows the Dutton family on a journey west through the Great Plains toward the last bastion of untamed America.

title: Tin Man
description: A re-imagining of L. Frank Baum's classic "The Wizard of Oz".

title: Little Woods
description: A modern Western about two sisters who work outside the law to better their lives.

title: The Undefeated
description: After the Civil War, ex-Confederate soldiers heading for a new life in Mexico run into ex-Union cavalrymen selling horses to the Mexican government but they must join forces to fight off Mexican bandits and revolutionaries.

title: Ride the High Country
description: An ex-union soldier is hired to transport gold from a mining community through dangerous territory. But what he doesn't realize is that his partner and old friend is plotting to double-cross him.

title: Geronimo: An American Legend
description: The story of the Apache chief and his armed resistance to the U.S. Government's subjugation of his people.

title: Support Your Local Sheriff!
description: In the old west, a man becomes a Sheriff just for the pay, figuring he can decamp if things get tough. In the end, he uses ingenuity instead.

title: Disturbing the Peace
description: A small-town marshal who hasn't carried a gun since he left the Texas Rangers after a tragic shooting, must pick up his gun again to battle with a gang of outlaw bikers that has invaded the town to pull off a brazen and violent heist.

title: The Duel
description: A Texas Ranger investigates a series of unexplained deaths in a town called Helena.

title: Johnny Guitar
description: After helping a wounded gang member, a strong-willed female saloon owner is wrongly suspected of murder and bank robbery by a lynch mob.

title: Fallout: New Vegas
description: After surviving a bullet to the head, Courier Six traverses the post-apocalyptic Mojave desert in search of the men who wronged him, while making an impact on thousands in the process.

title: Meek's Cutoff
description: Settlers traveling through the Oregon desert in 1845 find themselves stranded in harsh conditions.

title: Hannie Caulder
description: After she is raped and her husband murdered, a woman hires a bounty hunter to instruct her in the use of a gun so she can get her revenge on the three outlaws responsible.

title: Bandidas
description: In turn-of-the-century Mexico, two very different women become a bank-robbing duo in an effort to combat a ruthless enforcer terrorizing their town.

title: The Gold Rush
description: A prospector goes to the Klondike in search of gold and finds it and more.

title: The Fighting Kentuckian
description: In 1818 Alabama, French settlers are pitted against greedy land-grabber Blake Randolph but Kentucky militiaman John Breen, who's smitten with French gal Fleurette De Marchand, comes to the settlers' aid.

title: The Newton Boys
description: The story of the Newton gang, the most successful bank robbers in history, owing to their good planning and minimal violence.

title: Casey Jones
description: Television version of the classic train story of Casey Jones, the engineer of the steam-engine powered "Cannonball Express".

title: Bring Me the Head of Alfredo Garcia
description: An American bar room pianist and his prostitute girlfriend go on a trip through the Mexican underworld to collect a bounty on the head of a dead gigolo.

title: Here Come the Brides
description: The adventures of a logging work team and the marriageable single women sent to them in post-American Civil War Seattle in the Washington Territory.

title: Tell Them Willie Boy Is Here

title: Blackthorn

title: Shoot-Out at Medicine Bend
description: In Medicine Bend, a crooked businessman has the town mayor and sheriff in his pocket while his henchmen raid the wagon trains passing through the region.

title: Soleil rouge
description: In 1870, a gang robs a train and steals a ceremonial Japanese sword meant as a gift for the U.S. President, prompting a manhunt to retrieve it.

title: The Ballad of Lefty Brown
description: A thrilling and action-packed Western, The Ballad of Lefty Brown is a story about loyalty, friendship, and the relentless pursuit of justice.

title: Lone Wolf McQuade
description: After helping the local police with some horse thieves, a Texas Ranger aims at a drug lord with arms trade as well. They're interested in the same woman and they're both into martial arts.

title: They Came to Cordura
description: An army major, himself guilty of cowardice, is asked to recommend soldiers for the Congressional Medal of Honor during the Mexican Border Incursion of 1916.

title: Decision at Sundown
description: Bart Allison and sidekick Sam arrive in the town of Sundown on the wedding day of town boss Tate Kimbrough, whom Allison blames for his wife's death years earlier.

title: Comanche Moon
description: The adventures and love lives of young Texas Rangers Woodrow Call and Augustus McRae leading up to their retirement to the city of Lonesome Dove.

title: An American Tail: Fievel Goes West
description: A family of Emigre mice decide to move out to the West, unaware that they are falling into a trap perpetrated by a smooth-talking cat.

title: La resa dei conti
description: Unofficial lawman John Corbett hunts down Cuchillo Sanchez, a Mexican peasant accused of raping and killing a 12-year-old girl.

title: Daniel Boone

title: Zorro
